<Time>1564452414958<//Time>< Pictures>
None< /Pictures>
<review>Prices are  higher but it's expected considering the location in the Foothills. However, the staff is friendly, and, helpful, they have a variety of items from fresh fruits, and, veggies, to meats, frozen foods/desserts, other edibles, hot foods,  household goods, a gas station, etc. They even have specialty items that I can't even find at stores like Raleys, or, Walmart anymore! Better selection than the old Gold Eagle in Brownsville had before they burnt down.
If you can't get to the larger towns, or, don't want to make the long drive, this is the place to go! Highly recommended!<//review><user>108563848215867316058<//user><GmapID>0x809ca0197ae25289:0x37d7ad4fb8aa00bd</GmapID>< rating>

< review>
Love the employees, always so friendly and helpful. Love that they always have some awesome coca cola classic of course. But most importantly, the patrons that visit this store are some of the nicest folks.
The nice man behind me in line saw me walking home from the store and gave me a ride home. He doesn't know me for nothing and i was a hot sweaty mess... but out of the kindness that seems to be lacking in our society, he pulled over and drove me back to my spot.
Without spreading your name thank you kind sir... you save me from a long walk!
I am grateful and will be pay it forward once i get my truck working!
Love this town!< /review>

<text>Physically it is limited in space, but it caters to the Fellowship of Friends group of mostly foreigners with many of their products. It does have pretty much of what I need, though, when I go there, and is the most convenient store to my residence. They also have gas and diesel, which is very beneficial for all of us in the area since the other options are driving to Brownsville 8-10 miles away or to the 76 station at the highway 20 junction; another 13 miles away.. The people/workers are very friendly there, which I appreciate. It is also a place to gather, which in rural communities like ours is a plus. You can sit in the deli with your laptop and use their internet.< /text><rating>3< /rating>< gmap_id>

< Text>
I shop at the Oregon House Grocery Store almost on a daily basis. Living in the foothills you dont have alot of options. The prices are somewhat on the high side. The store also offers regular gasoline as well as diesal gas. They are open in the winter months from  7 am to 8pm. You can also get propane and cash in your recyclables.</Text>

<text>CHAPMAN AUTO REPAIR OF ORANGE is the name to remember whenever you need any kind of work done to your car.  Believe it or not, their company‚Äôs slogan is ‚ÄúThank you for calling the HAPPIEST place on earth, how can we help you today?‚Äù  At first I thought to myself that an Auto Repair place is like any other places and how can the company got Voted as the BEST of ORANGE for customer‚Äôs service and also Guarantee all of their repairs on PARTS and LABORS for LIFE.   Is that possible?  Is there such a place????

I then venture out to really find out if this place is real or are they just another advertisement scam like we all have seen, used to, and accustomed to receiving when it comes to dealing with auto repair companies.  After the worst possible experience I had with Lexus of Westminster, I have decided to give Chapman Auto Repair of Orange a try.  I found them online like most of us and believe me if you googled the company‚Äôs name you will be at ease after reading all the good comments left of this company.

From the first time talking to them until I left with my car LS 460 Lexus, I felt relieved for bringing my car here and to give them a try.  My Lexus needs a new starter and Lexus of Westminster quoted me the price of little over $2,200.00 to fix including the Diagnosis fees of $189.00 just to find out what the actual problem.  It took them 4 days later from the day of leaving my car to receiving a call back from them informing me my starter is the problem.  After the consultant Lance quoted me of the price $2,200 to fix the starter I confirmed with him once again about the warranty for their work and I was told of 12 months warranty on parts and labor and this is for replacing a ‚ÄúRE-MANUFACTURER‚Äù starter, not a brand new one.  I guess after 12 months and if the starter decided not to work again I will be out of another $2,200 for another starter.

With Chapman Auto Repair of Orange, the business is owned by John Pascal.  It is a family owned business and almost everyone who lives in Orange County knows who they are not because they are a big operator in the Auto Repairs space but most people know them through referral of friends, coworkers, or family members.  Don‚Äôt be fooled by taking your vehicle to the dealers as I thought my car will be safe with them when I pay higher prices.  This misconception is so wrong especially with Lexus of Westminster where their quoted prices of $2,200 to replace a starter, I got the exact same service from Chapman Auto Repair of Orange for $1,326.00 with LIFETIME WARRANTY ON PARTS & LABORS.  Yes, you heard that right, my starter is warrantied for life on parts and labors so I never have to replace another starter again.

John‚Äôs company also paid to have my car detailed all of inside, washed on the outside plus as complimentary he gave me a free oil change just to give them a try.  Now I am hook with their services and if I have to add up all of their combined services the cost of replacing my starter with them will be around $1,200.00 not counting the LIFETIME WARRANTY ON PARTS AND LABOR.  In many cases you have to pay extra for this type of insurance but with John‚Äôs company he told me that he uses great quality parts therefore he doesn‚Äôt mind giving lifetime warranty for the peace of mind to all of his customers.

What really melt my heart and felt warm about John and his staffs (Wesley, Joseph Robles, and Alan) is while I was there waiting for my car to be worked on, a homeless person walked in and was extremely apologetic by asking John if he could use the bathroom and not only John graciously agreed but also ask that the homeless person take with him some popcorn and a bottle of water with him after.  John did it with a smile instead of pushing him away.  I just wanted to take this opportunity to thank John Pascal (the owner), Joseph and Alan who helped signed me in, and Wesley who drove me to get a car rental while my car was worked on.

By proving this story is true I wanted to give my name and Michael T. Diep.  I am the inventor of Emery Cat Board.<//text>< GmapID>

<Text>As a female with not a lot of knowledge when it comes to cars, I was already feeling unsure about going into a new "Auto Repair Shop".  I thought to myself however, no matter what, you will eventually need to get some repairs done and the dealership will always be much higher in cost than a family-owned business. So I went ahead and scheduled an appointment with Chapman Auto Repair.

As soon as I walked in, I was completely impressed by not only the cleanliness of the facility, there were snacks, waters in a fridge and I was greeted with the most positive attitude -- it felt so genuine!  It wasn't just one staff member, I was greeted by 3-4 including some of the mechanics that were coming in and out of the main office.  I immediately felt at ease and welcomed.

Fortunately for me, I work right down the street so I was able to drop my car off at lunch, and get a ride to work and back to Chapman Auto Repair with the free shuttle service!

I returned to Chapman Auto Repair to see a list of items that my car would need to run smoother.  Even though I was budgeted for a few of those expenses, Chapman Auto Repair did not push me, they did not "sell me", they did set me up with a priority plan to fulfill all the line items over time and feeling confident that my car will run as smooth as it's able.  It felt like it was a family friend genuinely trying to help me get my car up-to-par.

Overall, my experience was very pleasant.  I was so pleased that I went back for a follow-up maintenance service several months later when it was time.  At that point, I was able to expense another line item on the plan.

I would highly recommend to anyone who needs work done for their car.  Chapman Auto Repair is warm, family-friendly, positive, they remember your name, and ultimately they look out for YOU and your car!  Thank you Chapman Auto Repair!</Text><pictures>None</pictures>< response>

We tried to visit here to get an alignment for our car after getting new tires.  We were told they are too busy and they asked us to set an appointment.  They offered a specific time 2 days later. We paid for the expected service and left.  Came back at the time they asked and they said they are too busy to do the work.  Perhaps we could come back another day.   WHAT?  And what would happen then?  They would look to see IF they could do it at that time. So what good is an appointment.  They said they only have one lift and they have always have a waiting list of cars that need it.   I asked for a refund of the money.  They refused.   So I had no choice but to file a fraud report with our credit card company who will charge them back and credit us that way.

Can not recommend this place.  They intentionally lie about appointment times and refuse to honor their own promises.  We ended up visiting Big-O to get the work done and they did it immediatly and at a cheaper price than Chapman wanted even after using their $40 off coupon we got from America's Tire.

--Additional info, next day--
The same representative that we dealt with at the time saw our review and called us on the phone to argue his point.    Having the employee involved call the customer to continue the argument is not a very good thing to do.

In their favor, a person identifying himself as the owner reached out to us and expressed regret at what transpired and assured us this is not what they want to see happen.  He offered to refund the amount immediately, something his employee would not do.   We returned the next day and received a check for the refund, but not until the employee from yesterday made a snide remark asking if we are going to remove the negative review.  He was told that we will edit the review adding this resolution.  Holding the check while asking that question and awaiting a reply felt like he was debating not giving us the check unless we agreed to remove the negative review.

In the end, We have upped the star rating from 1 to 3 based ONLY on the owners quick and appropriate response.</review>

<Text>Let me quickly set the scene. Me, my wife, and 2-year-old daughter take a spontaneous Saturday trip to Disneyland, leaving from Las Vegas. We don't pack a thing and head out. After a wonderful day, we see fireworks, gas up, and head home. With 5 lanes of dense traffic backed up for miles on the 91, my clutch goes out, and things get bad. I call several toe truck companies before one says, "Hey man, you need to call 911, like now." CHP arrives, shutting down the highway, and uses their car to push mine to the side. An interesting tow truck driver and a Best Western later, I drop my car off at Chapman's gate.

Now it's Sunday, and Chapman's is closed. I reach out the owner on Yelp, and he responds right away, saying, "I will get you taken care of first thing Monday morning." After another day at Disneyland, and another hotel room, I get to Chapman's bright and early.

I talk to Joe, who says he will check things out and see what we can do. I can tell Joe is a compassionate man who actually cares about getting my family home. Unfortunately, it's not a simple fix. It's going to take an entire clutch replacement which is usually a day and a half job. Joe hustles up and calls around for all the parts and luckily is able to find them. He says he will get me out the same day. A major relief.

Fun fact, Lyft and Uber, don't have car seats anywhere other than New York. We spend the day walking the streets of Orange and catch a movie. At 4pm, Joe calls to let me know they are buttoning things up and I should head down. We sit around a while and meet another interesting character, Frank, who keeps things light and lively while we wait.

Unfortunately, one of the parts is bad out of the box. We will have to stay another night. Frank offers to pay for our room and says they will get the part first thing in the morning. Best case scenario we are on the road by 10am, worst case, 3pm. I appreciate the blunt honesty throughout.

At 8am the next day, I get a call saying my car is ready to go. Joe and James, spent the entire night, until 9pm, taking my car back apart so they could get things done early in the morning and get my family on the road. It was James birthday to boot, and he spent it at work, helping me. That's the real deal. I won't forget it.

Big thanks to Joe, James, and Frank for taking care of me and going the extra mile. After four days in the same clothes and 15+ miles pushing a stroller around the streets of Orange, finally getting home is an indescribable feeling that I still may not have if it wasn't for these men.< /Text>< username>

If I could give zero stars i would
Please be aware --- be very aware
My car was towed, they checked it out and I was told the following"
I need to replace: water pump, thermostat, radiator hose top and bottom, and a belt = $1,600. I told them no deal and picked up my car. Took my car to my regular mechanic and I was told the following:
"That place is a rip off. The only thing you needed is a new clamp as the one on the radiator hose is defective". The clamp was replaced and my car has been fine ever since - in Total I spent $0.00. No, my mechanic does not believe in patch work. I use my car for work, so whatever I need to pay to have it repaired ....I would pa.

I will be honest, after their quote, i was worried that I would need to come out of pocket for at least $1,000 once i took it to my mechanic

I took my car there as it was recommended, but I was told, "they are expensive". The night before as I was driving home, I noticed that my engine warning light was on and the thermostat needle was reading hot. The car did not overheat. I also heard some squeaking and screeching which indicated a belt was wet. the belt can only be wet from a leak. However,  I did not notice any leakage. My radiator reservoir had no antifreeze and it took 3.5 bottles of arrowhead water. Definitely, something was wrong, but with my limited knowledge about auto repair - I figured, i would leave it to the experts. Not knowing that the experts were expert ripoffs.

They give you a line of credit (that's how they get you). I'm not foolish, I priced all the parts they listed - $650 which means $950 was labor costs.

I informed the person that recommended me , and trust after she pays what she owes.... she will never return. I won't ever go to them again, nor will I ever recommend them to anyone.

They didn't count on me knowing as much as I know about my car. I have been driving the same model car for 18 years (not the same car) and within that time I have gained some knowledge.

The only plus, since I dropped my friend's name , they did not charge me 89.99 to inspect the problem. LOL --- most likely because they knew that i would be back starting trouble to get a refund for misleading me and wanting me to give them $1,600 in exchange for a hose clamp.

I'm waiting for them to read this review and contact me so I can give them $1,600 worth of curse words.

Know your car, don;t be desperate, give AAA plus so you can tow your car past 7 miles. AAA is $75 for the year and you can tow up to 100 miles  --- well worth it !

Beware .... Be very Aware... DO NOT TAKE YOUR CAR THERE.... you have been warned. If you gon there and get ripped off ...you cannot say," I didn't know".

The "good reviews" are from people who didn't know any better. Their car was repaired because they were desperate and figured what they paid was a good deal.

You tell me ...who got the better deal....
$1,600 would have put my car back on the road, but so did a clamp that cost a buck and change. All the parts  that they requested to be repaired were in good working condition...considering I replaced the radiator one year ago, and my engine was replaced 45 days ago. So, if there were any issues my mechanic would have caught it.  In my model car, everything is so cramped that in order to get to the defective part, the surrounding parts require removal.

Please whenever anyone replaces parts on your car --- Be sure to get the old parts back as that is one indication that at least the part was changed out and not patched up and put back in.  That includes oil filters. Some mechanics will rise off the filter to get all the dust and dirty off then put in the same filter, although you were charged for a new one.

Take heed and scroll down to read a review from  2 months ago and another from 7 months ago - they both said the same thing as i just said about being over-priced and not needing to change out working parts .<//Text>

1459979366075< /time>
</record></dataset><record>
<Time>1444228200224<//Time><rating>1<//rating><name>Richard G</name>< Review>
If your older car breaks down on a weekend, don't have it towed to this facility.  My son's 2005 Jaguar X Type's water pumped seized and the pump drive belt broke.  I had the car towed to this facility because of the smiley faces and seemingly good reviews.

On Monday about noon Brien (that's how it's spelled!) texted me an estimate of a number of critical repairs that were urgently needed.  Of the eight items on the estimate not one of them was the seized water pump and broken belt!!!!!

So I called Brien and asked him about the original reason the car was brought in.  "Oh, the broken belt and seized water pump?"  Yes, can you give me an estimate for replacing the water pump, the water pump drive belt, and the serpentine belt? "I'll get right back to you"

$990.00 dollars for a water pump, water pump drive belt, and serpentine belt!!!  After a few minutes of blackness I came to and decided to come down to the shop and meet the crew..

Jaguar would have done it for a whole lot less.

This is not a difficult repair and I'm not a barefoot Pilgrim.  I decided not to do business with these people.  Now I was a bit surprised to receive a bill for $111.00 for the diagnostic estimate that they did on the car.  Biting the bullet because I had to have my car towed from the facility and I was feeling a bit exposed I paid the fee with my AMEX.  (I'm going to the BBB because I didn't ask for that diagnostic estimate)

I don't recall asking them to check my shocks or spark plugs.  I brought the car in with a seized water pump and broken belt.  That's just shady.

As to being friendly and perhaps the 'Happiest Place on Earth" these folks, including the new owner and his partner are smiling and very polite even when acknowledging that they are very expensive but they offer a 'lifetime' warranty and that's good value.

Such a shill.  Try and make good on that warranty if the car breaks down 50 miles from the shop.  Good luck.

So, my friends in Orange, don't fall for the bright paint and balloons, the kids dentist office toy box or the smiling faces of the happiest people on earth.

They're only happy when you're over a barrel and broke<//Review>

$900 + 2 weeks + a part I didn't need = nothing but Hot Air /// Some facts:  My A/C was 'pulsing' on and off (* cooling no more than 2-3 minutes at a time), incapable of bringing down the temp in my car cabin any further than near ambient (particularly during very hot days). I purchased a Groupon for an A/C system inspection and refill (if need be) at Chapman Auto Repair. After approx. 20 minutes, a member of the service team explained that he'd performed an A/C system leak check, charged the system with refrigerant "which was low" and insisted that a heating/cooling valve component needed to be replaced. 1 week later, I paid $850 (on top of the $50 Groupon), took receipt of my car and within the span of a weekend, my A/C began pulsing and then didn't work at all = nothing but hot air (* at any setting, having run 20+ minute tests on every possible setting with an outside temp of 100+F). I brought my car back, explained my concerns and Chapman agreed to take a look. Another week later, soon after speaking with a member of the Chapman front office - a conversation wherein it was suggested that I might not know what I'm talking about/there can't possibly be any merit to my claim (* I'm a university educated chemist, with a background in car tuning, construction, computer repair, new products development, woodworking...and chemistry), my car was delivered to me, idling, with the A/C on full and the lowest temperature setting, blowing nothing but HOT AIR!? Frustrated and told earlier that the team at Chapman felt certain that my car was repaired. I drove away, and drove straight to a mechanic with whom I worked with before. I cannot possibly state how surreal it was to receive my car in just as bad, if not worse, a condition as it was when I brought it in (2 weeks prior), with zero acknowledgment nor desire on the part of Chapman to get to the bottom of my cooling concerns. Note: I truly beg anyone at Chapman... I beg you to refute any of the above as being anything but the facts. At shop #2, the expert mechanic checked the A/C, explained to me that the refrigerant was near empyt, charged the system and performed a thorough leak check (including a UV light scan of any and all joints, junctions, known leak points throughtout the engine bay). Having found no sign of leaks whatsoever, he charged me $30 for the refrigerant and insisted that I drive the car for a week+ and report back. 3 weeks later, he checked the system again finding zero refrigerant lost, no leaks and the A/C working perfectly = comes on quickly (within seconds) and cools rapidly (despite the outside temp) aka. a fully functioning A/C. So what happened at Chapman? I'll honestly never know. Did they bother to fully charge the system? I can't say. Is their A/C diagnostic device broken? I have no idea. Was there a leak that somehow, miraculously repaired itself? It's unlikely. Did Chapman charge me $900 and deliver a car with an A/C system that inarguably didn't work (ex. hot air when delivered, empty refrigerant confirmed by second shop)? Yes, absolutely yes (and PLEASE Chapman, try to tell me I'm wrong. I would love to hear your input). P.S. I gave a tip to the second shop because of his absolute honesty, his desire to do right by his customers (he never once questioned my claims) and because his repair ACTUALLY WORKED - crazy, I know!< /review>

<Text>The staff here are really friendly and I feel they are honest. It is not the cheapest place to get auto repairs done, but I don't mind paying more for the best customer service and for my car being ready when they say it will be. I haven't used their complimentary shuttle, but they have offered it to me, which is really kind. They mail me coupons that I use. Their labor and parts are under a very reasonable warranty too.

< Review>
When we decided to replace our aging sedan, we did a number of internet searches for vehicles that fit our wants - we found quite a few nice-looking options at the Deal Time dealership in Bakersfield.  The staff responded very quickly to our multiple email inquiries, and we set a time to visit and look at the vehicles we liked from their ads.

From the time we arrived, the salespeople were exceptional - they showed us all 4 of the vehicles we were interested in, took us on test drives, and discussed the options with us, all without any ‚Äúpressure‚Äù to buy something.  In all, I think we dealt with 3 different sales people (Junior, Aldo, Alfonso if memory serves me) while we were checking out the different vehicles - one thing that amazed us was that each new salesperson we talked to knew what we were looking at, and where we were in the process (what we liked and what we didn‚Äôt).  It was great to have such a seamless transition between multiple different people!

When we decided on a specific SUV, the negotiation was effortless - the vehicle was priced right where Kelly Blue Book indicated, and we feel they gave us a more than fair offer on our trade-in.

Due to some time constraints, we had to leave the dealership before we could complete the transaction - but, that didn‚Äôt matter!  When we came back the next day, they had all the paperwork and our new SUV waiting for us, washed, cleaned, shiny, and ready to go.

Of course, we had our own mechanic go over the SUV.  Although it‚Äôs an older / classic model he told us it was in great shape, and didn‚Äôt identify any problems with it at all.

In all, we‚Äôre thrilled with the new car, and we‚Äôve never had a more positive car buying experience - we‚Äôd highly recommend Deal Time to anyone looking for a new vehicle.

Thanks for such a great experience!

<rating>5</rating>< Text>
The staff is extremely friendly, helpful, and efficient. I had recently purchased  a G-Shock watch, except the band was too big. I checked in to Fast Fix to have my watch adjusted to my wrist. Their clerk had me try on my watch to get an idea as to how many links they needed to remove. Their clerk told me that the adjustment would take roughly 20-25 minutes. I figured I'd kill some time at Macy's. Not even 10 minutes after I left the store, I receive a phone call from the Fast Fix staff, telling me that my watch is ready. I checked back in, and another employee had me try it on. Sure enough, my watch was now a perfect fit. The fair pricing and the great staff definitely earned my business!< /Text>

< Review>
Fast-Fix Jewelry has been in the a West Covina mall for as long as I can remember. They can fix any type of jewelry and I've even come to them multiple times for the same piece! Even though I did not buy my original rope chain from them, the staff was very knowledgeable and offered to explain why my chain kept breaking and possible options. They are so friendly and patient. They get the job done, call you when it's ready, get the repairs done in realistic and adequate time, they are honest, and have great prices. Fast-Fix Jewelry also works with you to get you an affordable price for any item and is not forceful or tries to make a sale. I won't go to anyone else for all my jewelry repairs! They log all your fixes and know what's been done to each piece. Most trustworthy business!< /Review>

I went to Old Navy today to return an item and I saw jeans for $10!! I didn't walk around because they were right by the line ... I thought yaaay, score!!!!
While in line in front of me a young lady was telling Michael "manager" that the price was incorrect. So he goes and checks it out and honors the price... Great!
My turn... Both the pants I picked (off the $10 rack) were not $10. Mind you, there was more than one of the same kind I picked on the rack, but different sizes!!
I proceed to tell Kathryn, the young lady helping me that they should honor the price because they were on the $10 rack!
Well, Michael "manager" said no. It really bummed me out! Why did he honor the young ladies items but not mine!?
I feel that was very unfair and I will be contacting corporate. I run a store, and I would rather honor a $5 price difference than loss $10 and a customer.
Michael is not a very good manager.< /Review>

I added almost everything to the bowl because I like my poke bowl to be very flavorful and usually get the whole shibang. However, this place doesn‚Äôt look like they have that option rather you select what you want. Mix-ins: onion and cucumber. Sauces: house sauce, ponzu, spicy ponzu, sesame oil, spicy mayo, and sweet chili. Sides: crab meat and seaweed salad. Toppings: green onion, cilantro, corn, edamame, Masago, crispy garlic, crispy onion. Drizzle: spicy mayo, eel sauce, lemon  garlic and sriracha on the side. Although I requested for almost close to everything, the bowl was still a bit dry and it did not seem like all the sauces I requested was added. Also they did not provide the sriracha on the side as requested. I‚Äôm not sure if they were busy or they just missed adding what was requested. The large bowl was very filling, so make sure you‚Äôre hungry if you get this size.

<rating>1</rating>< review>
I have taken vehicles here before back before they changed hands in 2016 and once after. I never had any problems before. They can fix your vehicle if they can figure what's wrong with it. My car has suspension problems. I have no check engine light and no super obvious broken parts dangling. So it makes it more difficult to figure out the problem. This was the third mechanic shop I took it to. My current experience with them was very disapointing the tech couldn't figure the main reason I brought it there for. I had to take it somewhere else. So I talked to someone via text who came off as unprofessional. I personally don't plan on dealing with them again.< /review>

<Rate>5</Rate><text>I was inspired to check out Mariners church after seeing how they helped my kids elementary school with donations of time and money as people at the church organized the community and church goers to give the school a facelift. I also saw Mariners extend open arms to all kids of people who were outcasts and fallen on hard times. As I researched the church I learned they had several campuses throughout Orange County.  I read some mixed reviews on google. I read a review from a local guide who apparently had never walked into the church itself. Inside the church I was greeted and offered help in finding where I was headed. The church has several ministries going that are extremely impactful to the community. I participated in a Mexico mission trip where the church has been serving for many years by helping children attend schools. I also observed a whole building at Mariners Irvine devoted to Student ministries for the upcoming youth. I also Noticed a whole Care and recovery building in Irvine open to anyone from any campus or any faith - devoted to multiple care and recovery platforms from Alcoholics Anonymous and Women's care and recovery ministries to Men battling sexual addiction. Never did I see a church or a set of people more interested in being in the community for the community than Mariners Church. Well done Mariners the work visible here is not of this world and that brings me to my last point. Humble leaders never pretending to be anything other than broken men and women seeking the Lord with all of their heart. I now call this church home and look forward to how the church and I will serve in the future.< /text>< Pics>

<user_id>110384934849005649584< /user_id><Name>Brutus Vincent<//Name><Time>1546528136068</Time>< Rating>
1</Rating>
< Text>
Attended for the first time 12.02.18 in the 11:30am service. The pastor named Jeff who spoke during this service chose to pander for laughs and likes from the congregation instead of presenting the Word of God with authority. Most of the service time consisted of him telling many silly personal stories with trivial details to appease the congregation instead of presenting the Word. Coddling the congregation and watering down God's Word is not the way to nurture the hungry souls of God's children. This service appeared to be more of a comedy hour to glorify pastor Jeff than a time to glorify and grow closer to Jesus. Jeff spent about 5 to 7 minutes at the end of the service actually speaking about some Biblcal information. Not once did he encouraged the congregation to bring a Bible or get a hold of a physical Bible if they did not own one. Phones, apps and slideshows are not an acceptable substitute to God's printed word. Pastoral service is not conforming to what we think that those congregated would like to hear, but speaking the truth without fear of what others might think. Being a pastor is not a role to which we are to seek to glorify ourselves like a Pharisee, it's about Jesus and what He's done for us. It's hard to understand that in a culture of self-absorbency like the one in Orange County. We don't come to a church to hear the pastor, we come to hear what GOD has to say to us. May you have eyes to see and ears to hear.

Some of the other reviews mention the ambiance and snacks. These are mere bread and circus my friends. The truth is if the staff, who are very much held accountable for every word that comes out of their mouths, are not feeding you God's unadulterated TRUTH they are not obeying God and are doing you zero good. It's easy to appease people with food, drink & comedy. Obeying God and delivering His Word is more challenging and the real point of gathering. A superficial and worldly church will comfort your body, a living church will cultivate your soul. Jeff and other pastoral staff: Will you be able to look back and testify before Father God that you did EVERYTHING He directed you to do in order to reach His children?

Being aware of the symbolism presented on your building or stage or property is important. Your decorations on stage were satanic pyramids with the all seeing eye.<//Text>
